attributeList.attribute: Defects in EGFR are associated with lung cancer [MIM:211980]

Subministration of AG1478 (a specific inhibitor of EGFR tyrosine kinase) inhibits both EGFR tyrosine phosphorylation and EGF-stimulated GRK2 binding to EGFR complex.

Pre-treatment of the cells with PP2 (a specific inhibitor of Src tyrosine kinase) decrease EGF-induced GRK2-EGFR complex formation. This result indicates that EGF-induced GRK2EGFR complex formation requires Src activity.

When the cells were transfected with Gt-alpha or GRK2ct the amount of GRK2 in the immunoprecipitation complex was greatly decreased
The formation of the GRK2-EGFR complex after EGF subministration is time dependent
After incubation with EGF, GRK2-GFP translocates to plasma membrane and become colocalized with EGFR. The formation of the GRK2-EGFR complex after EGF subministration is time dependent
